    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1893-08-19T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1893-08-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="629"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d629">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Gresham</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Terrell</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1893-08-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 19, 1893</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 41.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have received your No. 23, of the 29th ultimo,
                    concerning the complaint of Hyman Rose, an American citizen, in the matter of
                    the refusal of the authorities at Jerusalem to permit him to sell his real
                    estate.</p>
                <p>It would appear that the objections of the grand vizier lie against the
                    acquisition of lands by nonresidents for speculative purposes, and that in
                    imposing upon Mr. Rose an obligation to sell his land to “a citizen” or to “a
                    purchaser not an alien,” his excellency is not to be understood as announcing
                    any purpose to impede the bona ride purchase of lands in Turkey by American
                    citizens under the existing real estate protocol.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">W. Q. Gresham.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
